00072 L_AttrMngr *
00073 L_create_AttrMngr (char *fn_name, float weight)
00074 {
00075   L_AttrMngr *L_AM;
00076 
00077   if (!L_AttrMngr_pool)
00078     L_AttrMngr_pool =
00079       L_create_alloc_pool ("L_AttrMngr_pool", sizeof (L_AttrMngr), 1);
00080   if (!A_Attr_pool)
00081     A_Attr_pool = L_create_alloc_pool ("A_Attr_pool", sizeof (A_Attr), 1);
00082   L_AM = (L_AttrMngr *) L_alloc (L_AttrMngr_pool);
00083   L_AM->fn_name = strdup (fn_name);
00084   L_AM->fn_attr = L_AM->cb_attr = L_AM->op_attr = 0;
00085   L_AM->num_fn_attr = L_AM->num_cb_attr = L_AM->num_op_attr = 0;
00086   L_AM->weight = weight;
00087   return L_AM;
00088 }

00364 void
00365 L_write_attr_to_file (FILE * out, L_AttrMngr * func_attr)
00366 {
00367   A_Attr *this_attr;
00368   int i;
00369 
00370   if (fprintf (out, "# Attribute Manager file --- Version %d\n",
00371                AM_VERSION) < 0)
00372     {
00373       I_punt ("Attribute Manager cannot write to file");
00374       return;
00375     }
00376   fprintf (out, "begin %s %d %d %d %f\n", func_attr->fn_name,
00377            func_attr->num_fn_attr, func_attr->num_cb_attr,
00378            func_attr->num_op_attr, func_attr->weight);
00379   this_attr = func_attr->fn_attr;
00380   while (this_attr)
00381     {
00382       fprintf (out, "%s %d", this_attr->name, this_attr->num_fields);
00383       for (i = 0; i < this_attr->num_fields; i++)
00384         {
00385           if (!this_attr->field[i])
00386             fprintf (out, " NULL");
00387           else
00388             {
00389               switch (this_attr->field[i]->type)
00390                 {
00391                 case A_INT:
00392                   fprintf (out, " i %d", this_attr->field[i]->value.i);
00393                   break;
00394                 case A_FLOAT:
00395                   fprintf (out, " f %.3f", this_attr->field[i]->value.f);
00396                   break;
00397                 case A_STRING:
00398                   fprintf (out, " s %s", this_attr->field[i]->value.s);
00399                   break;
00400                 case A_LABEL:
00401                   fprintf (out, " l %s", this_attr->field[i]->value.l);
00402                   break;
00403                 default:
00404                   I_punt ("L_write_attr_to_file: Invalid attr type\n");
00405                 }
00406             }
00407         }
00408       fprintf (out, "\n");
00409       this_attr = this_attr->next_attr;
00410     }
00411   this_attr = func_attr->cb_attr;
00412   while (this_attr)
00413     {
00414       fprintf (out, "%d %s %d", this_attr->id_num, this_attr->name,
00415                this_attr->num_fields);
00416       for (i = 0; i < this_attr->num_fields; i++)
00417         {
00418           if (!this_attr->field[i])
00419             fprintf (out, " NULL");
00420           else
00421             {
00422               switch (this_attr->field[i]->type)
00423                 {
00424                 case A_INT:
00425                   fprintf (out, " i %d", this_attr->field[i]->value.i);
00426                   break;
00427                 case A_FLOAT:
00428                   fprintf (out, " f %.3f", this_attr->field[i]->value.f);
00429                   break;
00430                 case A_STRING:
00431                   fprintf (out, " s %s", this_attr->field[i]->value.s);
00432                   break;
00433                 case A_LABEL:
00434                   fprintf (out, " l %s", this_attr->field[i]->value.l);
00435                   break;
00436                 default:
00437                   I_punt ("L_write_attr_to_file: Invalid attr type\n");
00438                 }
00439             }
00440         }
00441       fprintf (out, "\n");
00442       this_attr = this_attr->next_attr;
00443     }
00444   this_attr = func_attr->op_attr;
00445   while (this_attr)
00446     {
00447       fprintf (out, "%d %s %d", this_attr->id_num, this_attr->name,
00448                this_attr->num_fields);
00449       for (i = 0; i < this_attr->num_fields; i++)
00450         {
00451           if (!this_attr->field[i])
00452             fprintf (out, " NULL");
00453           else
00454             {
00455               switch (this_attr->field[i]->type)
00456                 {
00457                 case A_INT:
00458                   fprintf (out, " i %d", this_attr->field[i]->value.i);
00459                   break;
00460                 case A_FLOAT:
00461                   fprintf (out, " f %.3f", this_attr->field[i]->value.f);
00462                   break;
00463                 case A_STRING:
00464                   fprintf (out, " s %s", this_attr->field[i]->value.s);
00465                   break;
00466                 case A_LABEL:
00467                   fprintf (out, " l %s", this_attr->field[i]->value.l);
00468                   break;
00469                 default:
00470                   I_punt
00471                     ("L_write_attr_to_file: Invalid attr %s (%d) type %d\n",
00472                      this_attr->name, i, this_attr->field[i]->type);
00473                 }
00474             }
00475         }
00476       if (this_attr->dep)
00477         fprintf (out, " %d\n", this_attr->dep);
00478       else
00479         fprintf (out, "\n");
00480       this_attr = this_attr->next_attr;
00481     }
00482   fprintf (out, "end %s\n\n", func_attr->fn_name);
00483 }

00494 void
00495 L_free_Attr (A_Attr * Attr)
00496 {
00497   A_Attr *this_attr, *next;
00498   int i;
00499 
00500   this_attr = Attr;
00501   while (this_attr)
00502     {
00503       next = this_attr->next_attr;
00504       for (i = 0; i < this_attr->num_fields; i++)
00505         if (this_attr->field[i])
00506           free (this_attr->field[i]);
00507       free (this_attr->field);
00508       L_free (A_Attr_pool, this_attr);
00509       this_attr = next;
00510     }
